SD-APPLET(1)          User Contributed Perl Documentation         SD-APPLET(1)



SYNOPSIS
       sd-applet, sd-files, sd-units

DESCRIPTION
       sd-applet is a small perl Gtk2 application that installs an icon into
       the system tray and provides the ability to manage systemd unit files
       and active units using a graphical interface.  It also provides for
       desktop notifications when unit files or the status of units changes.

       When invoked as sd-files, sd-applet pops up the files dialog.

       When invoked as sd-units, sd-applet pops up the units dialog.

SEE ALSO
       systemd(8)

LICENSE
       perl

AUTHOR
       Brian F. G. Bidulock <bidulock@openss7.org>



